      </FaqItem>
      <FaqItem question="Can I use a blade grinder for French press?">
        <p>You can, but cup quality is usually inconsistent because blade grinders create too many fines and boulders. A burr grinder is the better long-term fix.</p>
      </FaqItem>
      <FaqItem question="How do I reduce sludge/fines in my French press cup?">
        <p>Use a burr grinder at medium-coarse settings, avoid aggressive plunging, and let the brew settle for 60 seconds before pouring. Fewer fines in the grind is the biggest lever.</p>
      </FaqItem>
      <FaqItem question="How often should I clean my grinder for consistent taste?">
        <p>Do a quick brush clean every few brews and deep-clean monthly. Consistent cleaning reduces stale residue and keeps particle output stable over time.</p>
      </FaqItem>
    </FaqAccordion>
